{"segment_id": "laozi-chapter-048__chinesenotes-daodejing-zh-20260531__seg-001", "work_id": "laozi", "section_id": "laozi-chapter-048", "source_id": "laozi-chapter-048__chinesenotes-daodejing-zh-20260531", "language": "zh-Hant", "segment_type": "chapter", "segment_order": 1, "canonical_ref": "老子 48", "sort_key": "048.000", "text_original": "為學日益，\n\n為道日損。\n\n損之又損，以至於無為。無為而無不為。\n\n取天下常以無事，\n\n及其有事，\n\n不足以取天下。", "text_normalized": "為學日益，\n\n為道日損。\n\n損之又損，以至於無為。無為而無不為。\n\n取天下常以無事，\n\n及其有事，\n\n不足以取天下。", "notes": ""}
